		"biography":"<table><tr><td><b>HP</b> 182; <b>Bloodied</b> 91</td><td style=\"padding-left: 15px;\"><b>Init</b> +11</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center; background-color:lightgrey; padding:0px 5px 0px 5px;\"><table><tr style=\"border 0px; padding:0px 5px 0px 5px;\"><td><b>AC</b> 25</td><td><b>Fort</b> 25</td><td><b>Ref</b> 23</td><td><b>Will</b> 24</td></tr></table></td><td style=\"padding-left:15px;\"><b>Speed</b> 2 (earth walk)</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center; padding:0px 5px 0px 5px;\"><table><tr style=\"border 0px; padding:0px 5px 0px 5px;\"><td>Ability Scores</td><td><b>Str</b> 17 (+8)<br><b>Con</b> 19 (+9)</td><td><b>Dex</b> 15 (+7)<br><b>Int</b> 4 (+2)</td><td><b>Wis</b> 15 (+7)<br><b>Cha</b> 17 (+8)</td></tr></table><td style=\"padding-left:15px;\"><b>Languages</b> telepathy 10<br><b>Alignment</b> Unaligned</td></tr><tr><td><b>Skills</b> Stealth +12</td><td style=\"padding-left:15px;\"><b>Senses</b> <br><b>Passive</b> Perception 17 | Insight 17</td></td></tr></table><hr><table><tr><td><h4><b>Traits</b></h4></td></tr><tr><td><p style=\"background-color:green;color:white;\">[[/roll 0#&lt;p style=\"background-color:green;color:white;\"&gt; &lt;b&gt;Poison Fruit&lt;/b&gt; (charm) &lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The cactus bears between four and eight nectar-filled fruit. A creature can pick a fruit as a minor action and drink its liquid as a minor action. Any creature that drinks the liquid is dominated as if by the cactus’s dominating spores (save ends).&lt;/p&gt;]]  <b>Poison Fruit</b> (charm) <b></b></p><p>The cactus bears between four and eight nectar-filled fruit. A creature can pick a fruit as a minor action and drink its liquid as a minor action. Any creature that drinks the liquid is dominated as if by the cactus’s dominating spores (save ends).</p></tr></td><tr><td><h4><b>Standard</b></h4></td></tr><tr><td><p style=\"background-color:green;color:white;\">[[/roll 0#&lt;p style=\"background-color:green;color:white;\"&gt;(⚔) &lt;b&gt;Tendril&lt;/b&gt; (necrotic) ✦ &lt;b&gt;At-Will&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Attack:&lt;/i&gt; Melee 3 (one creature); +16 vs. AC&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Hit:&lt;/i&gt; 2d8 + 6 damage, and if the target is dominated by the cactus, it also takes ongoing 10 necrotic damage (save ends).&lt;/p&gt;]] (⚔) <b>Tendril</b> (necrotic) ✦ <b>At-Will</b></p><p><i>Attack:</i> Melee 3 (one creature); [[/roll 1d20+16[ vs. AC]#&lt;p style=\"background-color:green;color:white;\"&gt;(⚔) &lt;b&gt;Tendril&lt;/b&gt; (necrotic) ✦ &lt;b&gt;At-Will&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Attack:&lt;/i&gt; Melee 3 (one creature); &lt;u&gt;+16 vs. AC&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;]]</p><p><i>Hit:</i> [[/roll 2d8 + 6#&lt;p style=\"background-color:green;color:white;\"&gt;(⚔) &lt;b&gt;Tendril&lt;/b&gt; (necrotic) ✦ &lt;b&gt;At-Will&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Hit:&lt;/i&gt; 2d8 + 6 damage, and if the target is dominated by the cactus, it also takes ongoing 10 necrotic damage (save ends).&lt;/p&gt;]] <15>  damage, and if the target is dominated by the cactus, it also takes ongoing 10 necrotic damage (save ends).</p></tr></td><tr><td><p style=\"background-color:green;color:white;\">[[/roll 0#&lt;p style=\"background-color:green;color:white;\"&gt;⚔ &lt;b&gt;Lashing Tendrils&lt;/b&gt; ✦ &lt;b&gt;At-Will&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Effect:&lt;/i&gt; The cactus uses tendril twice, making each attack against a different target.&lt;/p&gt;]] ⚔ <b>Lashing Tendrils</b> ✦ <b>At-Will</b></p><p><i>Effect:</i> The cactus uses tendril twice, making each attack against a different target.</p></tr></td><tr><td><p style=\"background-color:darkred;color:white;\">[[/roll 0#&lt;p style=\"background-color:darkred;color:white;\"&gt;ᗕ &lt;b&gt;Dominating Spores&lt;/b&gt; (charm, zone) ✦ &lt;b&gt;Recharge&lt;/b&gt; when the cactus uses innocuous form&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Attack:&lt;/i&gt; Close burst 3 (enemies in the burst); +14 vs. Will&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Hit:&lt;/i&gt; The target is dominated (save ends). While at 0 hit points or fewer, the target cannot save against this power. When a creature dominated by the cactus dies, it becomes a zombie cactus thrall at the start of the zombie cactus’s next turn. The thrall acts immediately after the zombie cactus. The slain humanoid cannot be raised until the thrall is destroyed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Effect:&lt;/i&gt; The burst creates a zone that lasts until the end of the cactus’s next turn. Creatures dominated by the cactus that are within the zone take a -5 penalty to saving throws against this power.&lt;/p&gt;]] ᗕ <b>Dominating Spores</b> (charm, zone) ✦ <b>Recharge</b> when the cactus uses innocuous form</p><p><i>Attack:</i> Close burst 3 (enemies in the burst); [[/roll 1d20+14[ vs. Will]#&lt;p style=\"background-color:darkred;color:white;\"&gt;ᗕ &lt;b&gt;Dominating Spores&lt;/b&gt; (charm, zone) ✦ &lt;b&gt;Recharge&lt;/b&gt; when the cactus uses innocuous form&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Attack:&lt;/i&gt; Close burst 3 (enemies in the burst); &lt;u&gt;+14 vs. Will&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;]]</p><p><i>Hit:</i> The target is dominated (save ends). While at 0 hit points or fewer, the target cannot save against this power. When a creature dominated by the cactus dies, it becomes a zombie cactus thrall at the start of the zombie cactus’s next turn. The thrall acts immediately after the zombie cactus. The slain humanoid cannot be raised until the thrall is destroyed.</p><p><i>Effect:</i> The burst creates a zone that lasts until the end of the cactus’s next turn. Creatures dominated by the cactus that are within the zone take a -5 penalty to saving throws against this power.</p></tr></td><tr><td><p style=\"background-color:green;color:white;\">[[/roll 0#&lt;p style=\"background-color:green;color:white;\"&gt; &lt;b&gt;Innocuous Form&lt;/b&gt; ✦ &lt;b&gt;At-Will&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Effect:&lt;/i&gt; The cactus changes its form to resemble a flowering oasis cactus (DC 27 Nature check to notice the difference). While in this form, it gains resist 15 to all damage and regeneration 5, and it can take no actions other than to revert to its normal form as a minor action.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Regeneration 5:&lt;/i&gt; The cactus regains 5 hit points whenever it starts its turn and has at least 1 hit point.&lt;/p&gt;]]  <b>Innocuous Form</b> ✦ <b>At-Will</b></p><p><i>Effect:</i> The cactus changes its form to resemble a flowering oasis cactus (DC 27 Nature check to notice the difference). While in this form, it gains resist 15 to all damage and regeneration 5, and it can take no actions other than to revert to its normal form as a minor action.</p><p><i>Regeneration 5:</i> The cactus regains 5 hit points whenever it starts its turn and has at least 1 hit point.</p></tr></td></table>",
